      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the Navier-Stokes and hemolysis transport equations on three canonical geometries. Observed convergence rates match theoretical second-order accuracy for velocity and pressure; hemolysis scalar transport converges at first-order due to upwind advection scheme. All residuals within solver tolerance. Results documented in code verification report CVR-2024-001.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
