      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "GCI study on three systematically refined meshes (refinement ratio 2.0) yields fine-grid GCI of 1.4% for NIH. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Wall y+ maintained between 1 and 5 on all wetted surfaces of the 33.6 M element mesh used for production runs. Discretization error is the second-smallest contributor to the total uncertainty budget (2.1%).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/discretization-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
