      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were conducted in an ISO 10993-4-compliant blood-analogue loop at 37 ± 0.5 °C, using porcine blood with hematocrit 40 ± 2%, and measured by the modified Cripps photometric method. Flow rate controlled to ±0.05 L/min via Coriolis meter; pressure transducers calibrated to ±0.5 mmHg. Pump rotational speed verified by optical tachometer ±5 RPM. All test conditions are documented in test protocol TP-VAD-2023-07.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/test-conditions",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with measurement uncertainty for all controlled variables. Hematocrit, temperature, flow rate, and speed must each be reported with expanded uncertainty (k=2). Test protocol must be traceable to a calibrated measurement system."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using the area validation metric (AVM) and the U95 band overlap criterion per ASME V&V 20-2009. At all five operating points the CFD prediction lies within the experimental expanded uncertainty band. Mean MAPE of 6.2% is below the 10% acceptance threshold. Comparison plots with error bars and prediction intervals are archived in validation report VR-COU2-2024.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/output-comparison",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "CFD predictions must fall within the experimental expanded uncertainty band (k=2) at ≥80% of validation points. MAPE must be ≤10% across all five operating points. Comparison must use a standardized validation metric documented in the validation report."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, g/100 L), which is the direct regulatory metric for hemolysis acceptance per ASTM F1841. The CFD model directly computes NIH via the power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. No surrogate or proxy QoI is used; the computed quantity maps directly to the clinical threshold assessment.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/qoi-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "The QoI computed by the model must be the same metric used in the regulatory acceptance criterion. Any transformation between model output and regulatory metric must be explicitly documented and its uncertainty quantified."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at operating conditions spanning the full COU envelope (2–8 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM). Blood analogue properties match COU specifications. The validation dataset covers all five COU operating points directly; no extrapolation from a different geometry or fluid is required. Validation-to-COU similarity score assessed as HIGH per Morrison Table 3 criteria.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/validation-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Validation activities must cover the same pump geometry, fluid properties within ±15%, and operating conditions spanning the COU envelope. At least 80% of COU operating points must be directly covered by validation data without extrapolation."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
