      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms and QoI monitors. All simulations converged to residual norms below 1×10⁻⁶ for continuity and momentum; NIH monitor stabilized to within 0.05% over the final 500 iterations. Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic throughout; floating-point sensitivity study confirms negligible impact on NIH (<0.01%). Solver error contribution to total uncertainty budget: 0.3%.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/solver-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Iterative residuals must reach ≤1×10⁻5 for all transport equations. QoI monitor must stabilize to within 0.1% over the final 10% of iterations. Double-precision arithmetic must be used throughout. Solver error contribution to total uncertainty budget must be documented."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
