      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "CFD boundary conditions were set to match experimental test conditions within measurement uncertainty for all controlled variables: flow rate within ±0.05 L/min (CFD inlet velocity profile matched to Coriolis meter reading), rotational speed within ±5 RPM, inlet temperature 37 °C, hematocrit 40%. Pump geometry in CFD was derived from CMM-verified CAD model with dimensional tolerances ≤0.05 mm. Equivalency verified by a parameter-by-parameter comparison table in validation report VR-COU2-2024, Section 4.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/input-equivalency",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "CFD boundary conditions must match experimental conditions within measurement uncertainty for all controlled variables. A parameter-by-parameter equivalency table must be included in the validation report. Geometric fidelity must be confirmed by CMM measurement of the tested specimens."
